                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 18th century – the first half of the 19th
                           century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; a few lines
                           (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of Texts I and II;
                           groups of lines (alternating with black lines) of the incipit of Text II;
                           incipits of sections/miracles; word salām “salutation” in Text III;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals and their
                           elements.</seg>
                        <note>In <locus from="53vb" to="54ra">53vb-54ra</locus> the letters have
                           narrower strokes since the scribe used a thinner nib. </note>
                        <note>The 6th order vowel marker of ጵ is attached to the upper vertical
                           stroke at the left side (e.g., <locus target="#26vb">26vb</locus>).</note>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>
                           <desc type="Unclear">: Barely readable note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <note> The note, written in red ink, is barely readable. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>
                           <desc type="PurchaseNote">Purchase note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘመምህሬ፡ ገብረ፡ ወልድ፡ ወስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ መምህር፡ ተ&lt;…&gt;፡
                              ዘአጥረዮ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ከመ፡ ይኵኖ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወስጋ።</q>
                           <note> The note states that the Ms. was bought by <persName role="owner" ref="PRS12105GabraWald">
                                 <roleName type="title">mamhǝre</roleName>
                                 Gabra Wald</persName>. His father’s name is for the most part
                              unreadable. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#78vb">f. 78vb</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘእቍባ፡ ጊዎርጊስ[sic]፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለማርያም፡ ህርጉድ(?)፡ ከመ፡
                              ትኵኖ፡ መርሐ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ያት[sic]፡ ምስለ፡ አቡሁ፡ ኪዓደ(?)፡ ማርያም፡ ወምስለ፡ እሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ዮሐንስ፡
                              ወምስለ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ወልደ፡ ጊዎጊስ[sic]፡ አምኃ፡ ጊዎርጊስ፡ መድኅን፡ ባር[sic]፡ ነጋሽ፡
                              ዘጊዎርጊስ፡ ሰያጢ፡ አባ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ ዘደብረ፡ አቡነ፡ መርቆርየዎስ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ…</q>
                           <note> The note is written in the main hand. It states that the Ms. was
                              donated by <persName role="donor" ref="PRS12106EqwbaGiorgis">ʿƎqwǝba
                                 Giworgis</persName> to the Church of <placeName type="church" ref="LOC7015MaryamHergwed">Māryām Hǝrgwǝd</placeName> (?). Also,
                              the donor’s family members are mentioned: his father <persName ref="PRS12107Kiada">Kiʿāda (?) Māryām</persName>, his mother
                                 <persName ref="PRS12108Walatta">Walatta Yoḥannǝs</persName> as well
                              as children <persName ref="PRS12109WaldaMaryam">Walda
                                 Māryām</persName>, <persName ref="PRS12110WaldaG">Walda
                                 Giworgis</persName>, <persName ref="PRS12111Amha">ʾAmḫā Giworgis
                                 Madḫǝn</persName> and <persName ref="PRS12112Zagiworgis">
                                 <roleName type="office">bār (bāḥr) nagāš</roleName>
                              Za-Giworgis</persName>. The seller is <persName ref="PRS12113Salomon" role="scribe">
                                 <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName>
                                 Salomon</persName> of Dabra ʾAbuna Marqoryewos (possibly the
                              monastery <placeName ref="INS0349EM">Dabra Dǝmāḥ, Sarāye</placeName>),
                              who might be also the scribe. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters, words, lines or passages are written
                           interlineally, in secondary hands: e.g., <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>b, 7vb, 8vb, 9rab, 11rb, 15ra, 16va, 22ra, 27vb, 29va, 35rab,
                           47ra, 72ra.&#xD;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"> - The content of the Ms. is written in pen on <locus target="#57r">57r</locus>. &#xD;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"> - A name “halaqā ʾAbrǝhā” is written in bold letters, in
                           pen on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.&#xD;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"> - Numbers are crudely written in pen in the upper margin
                           of all fols. &#xD;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"> - Minor notes, writing exercises, doodles: e.g., <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus>, 2rv, 3rv, 4r, 5v, 54r, 57rv, 79rv.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards (the front board is broken and
                           repaired; 30% is missing). &#xD; Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes or tears are visible in the
                           centre fold of the quires, close to the head and tail of the
                           codex.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">A crude design of the cross has been scored in both
                           the boards.</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
