               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="INS0103AKM"/>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1850">Second half of the 18th cent. to the
                        first half of the 19th cent.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The original donor is <persName role="donor" ref="PRS12106EqwbaGiorgis">ʿƎqwǝba Giworgis</persName> mentioned in <ref target="#a3">Additio 3</ref> together with some of his family members. Also,
                     their names are written in the supplications formulas over erasures, in the
                     main hand (?): ʿƎqwǝba Giworgis (e.g., <locus target="#50vb">50vb</locus>,
                     59vb, 61ra, 62rb, 64vb, 65ra), his wife <persName ref="PRS12114Maharit">Maḥārit/Maḥārti Māryām</persName> (e.g., <locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>,
                     59vb, 65ra), <persName ref="PRS12111Amha">ʾAmḫā Giworgis</persName> (e.g.,
                        <locus target="#58ra">58ra</locus>, 71ra), <persName ref="PRS12110WaldaG">Walda Giworgis</persName> (e.g., <locus target="#62rb">62rb</locus>, 70vb),
                     Walatta Māryām (e.g., <locus target="#64va">64va</locus>).&#xD; Later the Ms.
                     was purchased by <persName role="owner" ref="PRS12105GabraWald">
                        <roleName type="title">mamhǝre</roleName> Gabra Wald</persName> (s. <ref target="#a2">Additio 2</ref>). At some point the name of another person,
                        <persName ref="PRS12115GabraM" role="owner">Gabra Madḫǝn</persName>, was
                     written interlineally above or below the supplication formulas on <locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>, 50vb, 58ra, 78vb.&#xD; According to <ref target="#a3">Additio 3</ref>, the book was originally donated to the Church
                     of <placeName type="church" ref="LOC7015MaryamHergwed">Māryām
                        Hǝrgwǝd</placeName> (?).</provenance>
               </history>
